<div class=3D"body-text-component text-container"><p>At ZOWIE, we understan=
d that in fast-paced FPS games like Valorant, APEX Legends, and CS2, every =
fraction of a second matters. That=E2=80=99s why eDPI=E2=80=94the key to un=
locking your true potential=E2=80=94plays a crucial role in your gameplay. =
Unlike simple DPI, eDPI combines your mouse=E2=80=99s DPI and your in-game =
sensitivity, giving you the perfect balance of precision and speed to take =
down your enemies faster and more accurately.</p>
<p>But knowing your eDPI alone won=E2=80=99t cut it. To dominate the compet=
ition, you need a FPS mouse that complements your settings and delivers the=
 performance you demand. In this article, we=E2=80=99ll dive into the impor=
tance of eDPI, how to calculate it, and why the right mouse is essential fo=
r leveling up your skills and pushing your limits in FPS games.</p>
</div>

   =20





</div>
<div class=3D"section-title-subtitle aem-GridColumn aem-GridColumn--default=
--12">





   =20
   =20
<link rel=3D"stylesheet" href=3D"https://zowie.benq.com/etc.clientlibs/comm=
on/clientlibs/clientlib-components/section-title-subtitle/game-section-titl=
e-subtitle.min.d06fbc5398abf87268e73e099ef5b071.css" type=3D"text/css">








<div class=3D"section-title-component" id=3D"active">
   =20
    <h2 class=3D"section-title" id=3D"subtitle-jump-0">
        What is eDPI? =20
    </h2>
   =20
   =20
</div>

</div>
<div class=3D"body-text aem-GridColumn aem-GridColumn--default--12">






   =20
   =20






<div class=3D"body-text-component text-container"><p>eDPI, or effective DPI=
, is the combination of your mouse's DPI (dots per inch) and your in-game m=
ouse sensitivity, giving you a more precise understanding of your mouse=E2=
=80=99s true sensitivity during gameplay. Unlike DPI alone, which only tell=
s you how far your mouse moves physically, eDPI also factors in how your in=
-game mouse sensitivity influences that movement on-screen.</p>
<p>In simple terms, eDPI reveals how quickly or slowly your crosshair moves=
, taking into account both the DPI of your mouse and the sensitivity settin=
gs inside the game. This makes eDPI an essential tool for fine-tuning your =
mouse settings, helping you achieve that perfect balance of speed and accur=
acy for peak performance in FPS games</p>
</div>

   =20




</div>
<div class=3D"section-title-subtitle aem-GridColumn aem-GridColumn--default=
--12">





   =20
   =20








<div class=3D"section-title-component" id=3D"active">
   =20
    <h2 class=3D"section-title" id=3D"subtitle-jump-1">
        What is DPI
    </h2>
   =20
   =20
</div>

</div>
<div class=3D"body-text aem-GridColumn aem-GridColumn--default--12">






   =20
   =20






<div class=3D"body-text-component text-container"><p>DPI, or dots per inch,=
 is a measurement that defines how sensitive a mouse is, indicating how far=
 your cursor moves on-screen based on the physical movement of the mouse. W=
hile a higher DPI allows for quicker, broader movements, it doesn=E2=80=99t=
 always equate to better control. The problem with relying solely on DPI is=
 that it overlooks how your in-game sensitivity settings interact with your=
 mouse=E2=80=99s performance.</p>
<p>Focusing on DPI alone without considering eDPI might lead to settings th=
at feel too fast or too slow for effective gameplay. It's important to reme=
mber that eDPI offers a more complete understanding of your sensitivity, wh=
ich is why it=E2=80=99s crucial for fine-tuning your mouse settings for opt=
imal FPS game performance.</p>
</div>

   =20




</div>
<div class=3D"section-title-subtitle aem-GridColumn aem-GridColumn--default=
--12">





   =20
   =20








<div class=3D"section-title-component" id=3D"active">
   =20
    <h2 class=3D"section-title" id=3D"subtitle-jump-2">
        What is in-game sensitivity mouse sensitivity
    </h2>
   =20
   =20
</div>

</div>
<div class=3D"body-text aem-GridColumn aem-GridColumn--default--12">






   =20
   =20






<div class=3D"body-text-component text-container"><p>In-game mouse sensitiv=
ity is a software setting that controls how much your crosshair moves in re=
sponse to your physical mouse movements. While DPI measures the hardware-le=
vel sensitivity of your mouse, in-game mouse sensitivity adjusts that input=
 within the game. Higher in-game sensitivity results in faster movements, w=
hile lower sensitivity allows for finer control.</p>
<p>However, relying solely on in-game mouse sensitivity can be problematic.=
 FPS Games often use different sensitivity scales, making it difficult to m=
aintain consistent aim across FPS game titles like Valorant, APEX Legends, =
or CS2. This is where eDPI (effective DPI) becomes essential, providing a s=
tandardized measurement that reflects your true aiming sensitivity by combi=
ning both your mouse=E2=80=99s DPI and in-game sensitivity.</p>
</div>

   =20




</div>
<div class=3D"section-title-subtitle aem-GridColumn aem-GridColumn--default=
--12">





   =20
   =20








<div class=3D"section-title-component" id=3D"active">
   =20
    <h2 class=3D"section-title" id=3D"subtitle-jump-3">
        eDPI vs DPI vs In-Game Mouse Sensitivity=20
    </h2>
   =20
   =20
</div>

</div>
<div class=3D"body-text aem-GridColumn aem-GridColumn--default--12">






   =20
   =20






<div class=3D"body-text-component text-container"><p>In FPS games like Valo=
rant, APEX Legends, and CS2, mastering your mouse sensitivity is essential =
for precise aiming. Understanding the differences between eDPI, DPI, and in=
-game mouse sensitivity will help you find the perfect balance for better c=
ontrol and accuracy.</p>
</div>

   =20




</div>
<div class=3D"section-title-subtitle aem-GridColumn aem-GridColumn--default=
--12">





   =20
   =20








<div class=3D"section-title-component">
   =20
   =20
    <h3 class=3D"section-subtitle">DPI (Dots Per Inch): </h3>
   =20
</div>

</div>
<div class=3D"body-text aem-GridColumn aem-GridColumn--default--12">






   =20
   =20






<div class=3D"body-text-component text-container"><p>DPI measures how far y=
our cursor moves based on your physical mouse movement.</p>
</div>

   =20




</div>
<div class=3D"section-title-subtitle aem-GridColumn aem-GridColumn--default=
