<div class=3D"section-title-component" id=3D"active">
   =20
    <h2 class=3D"section-title" id=3D"subtitle-jump-4">
        Why is eDPI more important than DPI for FPS games?=20
    </h2>
   =20
   =20
</div>

</div>
<div class=3D"body-text aem-GridColumn aem-GridColumn--default--12">






   =20
   =20






<div class=3D"body-text-component text-container"><p>In FPS games, eDPI is =
the key metric that pro players focus on. While DPI might matter in other g=
enres, eDPI is what truly defines performance in fast-paced shooters like V=
alorant, CS2, and Apex Legends. By combining both the mouse DPI and in-game=
 sensitivity, eDPI ensures the perfect balance of speed and accuracy for pr=
ecise aiming.</p>
<p>Pro players know that mastering eDPI is essential for elite-level gamepl=
ay. In FPS games, where every millisecond matters, eDPI is the ultimate mea=
sure of control. It=E2=80=99s not just about how fast your mouse moves, but=
 how accurately you can track and hit targets. In FPS games, eDPI is the tr=
ue benchmark for achieving pinpoint precision in your shots.</p>
</div>

   =20




</div>
<div class=3D"section-title-subtitle aem-GridColumn aem-GridColumn--default=
--12">





   =20
   =20








<div class=3D"section-title-component" id=3D"active">
   =20
    <h2 class=3D"section-title" id=3D"subtitle-jump-5">
        How to calculate eDPI?=20
    </h2>
   =20
   =20
</div>

</div>
<div class=3D"body-text aem-GridColumn aem-GridColumn--default--12">






   =20
   =20






<div class=3D"body-text-component text-container"><p>To calculate your eDPI=
 (effective DPI), you need two key values: your mouse's DPI and your in-gam=
e sensitivity. The formula is simple:</p>
<p><b>eDPI =3D DPI =C3=97 In-Game Mouse Sensitivity</b></p>
</div>

   =20




</div>
<div class=3D"section-title-subtitle aem-GridColumn aem-GridColumn--default=
--12">





   =20
   =20








<div class=3D"section-title-component" id=3D"active">
   =20
    <h2 class=3D"section-title" id=3D"subtitle-jump-6">
        eDPI Calculation Example:=20
    </h2>
   =20
   =20
</div>

</div>
<div class=3D"body-text aem-GridColumn aem-GridColumn--default--12">






   =20
   =20






<div class=3D"body-text-component text-container"><p>Let's use PRX somethin=
g as an example.</p>
<ul>
<li><p>DPI: 800</p>
</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><p>In-Game Mouse Sensitivity: 0.66</p>
</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><p>eDPI =3D 800 =C3=97 0.66 =3D 528.00&nbsp;</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p>In this case, PRX something has an eDPI of 528.00, which gives a clear i=
dea of how sensitive his mouse is when playing Valorant. This eDPI value en=
sures they have the right balance of speed and accuracy, crucial for precis=
e aiming in high-stakes gameplay.</p>
</div>

   =20




</div>
<div class=3D"section-title-subtitle aem-GridColumn aem-GridColumn--default=
--12">





   =20
   =20








<div class=3D"section-title-component" id=3D"active">
   =20
    <h2 class=3D"section-title" id=3D"subtitle-jump-7">
        Adjustable vs. Fixed DPI: Which is Better for FPS Games?=20
    </h2>
   =20
   =20
</div>

</div>
<div class=3D"body-text aem-GridColumn aem-GridColumn--default--12">






   =20
   =20






<div class=3D"body-text-component text-container"><p>In FPS games, flexibil=
ity in DPI isn't as crucial as finding the optimal eDPI balance. Fixed DPI =
settings like 400, 800, or 1600 are common in gaming mice, providing a stab=
le sensitivity range. However, some players may prefer adjustable DPI to ha=
ve finer control over DPI increments, especially for specific scenarios.&nb=
sp;</p>
<p>While adjustable DPI gives more flexibility, it doesn=E2=80=99t directly=
 enhance FPS game performance. What truly matters is adjusting your in-game=
 mouse sensitivity to fine-tune your eDPI. This allows you to directly cont=
rol and adapt your mouse sensitivity in the game's environment. Compared to=
 adjusting DPI through software, in-game mouse sensitivity adjustments are =
faster and more responsive, giving you immediate feedback. Ultimately, the =
right eDPI balance is what truly affects your performance, ensuring better =
precision and control during gameplay.</p>
</div>

   =20




</div>
<div class=3D"section-title-subtitle aem-GridColumn aem-GridColumn--default=
--12">





   =20
   =20








<div class=3D"section-title-component" id=3D"active">
   =20
    <h2 class=3D"section-title" id=3D"subtitle-jump-8">
        What's the ideal eDPI for FPS games like Valorant?=20
    </h2>
   =20
   =20
</div>

</div>
<div class=3D"body-text aem-GridColumn aem-GridColumn--default--12">






   =20
   =20






<div class=3D"body-text-component text-container"><p>In FPS games like Valo=
rant, eDPI is highly individual, but overall trends emerge from pro player =
data. The average eDPI for pros tends to be in the range of 200-450, with t=
he mean around 282 and the median at 256. For example, PRX Something has an=
 eDPI of 528, while EDG ZmjjKK is much lower at 160, and PRX Jinggg sits at=
 312, which is within the average range.</p>
<p>While these numbers give a general idea of what works for the majority o=
f pro players, eDPI is still a personal preference. Finding the right balan=
ce between speed and accuracy depends on your unique playstyle and comfort.=
</p>
</div>

   =20




</div>
<div class=3D"section-title-subtitle aem-GridColumn aem-GridColumn--default=
--12">





   =20
   =20








<div class=3D"section-title-component" id=3D"active">
   =20
    <h2 class=3D"section-title" id=3D"subtitle-jump-9">
        To Maximize eDPI: Why You Need a True FPS Mouse Designed for FPS Ga=
mes=20
    </h2>
   =20
   =20
</div>

</div>
<div class=3D"body-text aem-GridColumn aem-GridColumn--default--12">






   =20
   =20






<div class=3D"body-text-component text-container"><p>At ZOWIE, we understan=
d that while optimizing eDPI is crucial for FPS performance, choosing the r=
ight FPS mouse is just as important. That's why we don=E2=80=99t guess what=
 works best=E2=80=94we gather real-world data and leverage sports science t=
o create mice specifically designed for FPS players.</p>
<p>We recognize that every player has unique preferences when it comes to g=
rip style, movement, and sensitivity. That=E2=80=99s why each of our FPS mi=
ce is crafted to strike the perfect balance of comfort and control. By anal=
yzing data from professional players, we ensure that our designs offer the =
stability, precision, and responsiveness necessary to maximize your eDPI an=
d elevate your gameplay. With a ZOWIE FPS mouse, you're not just tweaking s=
ettings=E2=80=94you=E2=80=99re using a mouse built for high-level FPS perfo=
rmance.</p>
</div>

   =20




</div>
